I"°<h2 id="problem">Problem</h2>
<p>When a connected USB disk doesn‚Äôt show up in <code class="highlighter-rouge">Finder</code> and <code class="highlighter-rouge">Disk Utility</code> ‚Äú<em>Loading disks</em>‚Äù forever, this is happening most likely due to a long-running <code class="highlighter-rouge">fsck</code> process.</p>

<h2 id="solution">Solution</h2>
<p>Kill the <code class="highlighter-rouge">fsck</code> process:</p>
<div class="language-bash highlighter-rouge"><div class="highlight"><pre class="highlight"><code><span class="nb">sudo kill</span> <span class="si">$(</span>ps <span class="nt">-ef</span> | <span class="nb">awk</span> <span class="s1">'/fsck/ {print $2}'</span><span class="si">)</span> 2&gt;/dev/null
</code></pre></div></div>

